      "name": "High CPU Utilization",
      "description": "This alert is triggered when CPU Utilization exceeds the defined threshold. This could indicate high workload, inefficient resource allocation, or potential performance degradation.\n\nThe alert is activated when `CPU Utilization` exceeds the threshold for more than 10 minutes.\n\nCustomisation Guidance:\n  - Threshold: Trigger when `CPUUtilization` exceeds the defined limit for more than 10 minutes. Currently defined threshold is 80%.  \n  - Monitoring Period: Adjust based on workload patterns and scaling requirements.\n  - Notification Frequency: Ensure repeated alerts are minimised to avoid noise.\n\nAction: Investigate the impacted resource, analyse running processes, and consider scaling or optimising workload distribution.",
      "enabled": true,
      "priority": "ALERT_DEF_PRIORITY_P3",
      "type": "ALERT_DEF_TYPE_METRIC_THRESHOLD",
      "groupByKeys": [
